1267
01:07:54,880 --> 01:07:57,530
Yes. Uh, <i>si.</i>

1268
01:08:00,450 --> 01:08:04,290
Miguel, uh,
my reputation...

1269
01:08:04,290 --> 01:08:07,760
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES)</font> It is
very important to me.

1270
01:08:07,760 --> 01:08:09,860
I would hate
to have you think...

1271
01:08:09,860 --> 01:08:13,900
That you murdered Hector
for his songs?

1272
01:08:13,900 --> 01:08:15,340
<font color="#ff00ff">(LAUGHS)</font>

1273
01:08:15,340 --> 01:08:18,640
You don't think that.
Do you?

1274
01:08:18,640 --> 01:08:23,620
<font color="#ff00ff">(STAMMERS)</font> I... No. Everyone
knows you're the good guy.

1275
01:08:29,850 --> 01:08:32,930
<i>Papa</i> Ernesto, my blessing?

1276
01:08:34,890 --> 01:08:39,660
Security? Take care of Miguel.
He'll be extending his stay.

1277
01:08:39,660 --> 01:08:42,800
What? But I'm your family!

1278
01:08:42,800 --> 01:08:45,370
And Hector
was my best friend.

1279
01:08:45,370 --> 01:08:48,770
Success doesn't
come for free, Miguel.

1280
01:08:48,770 --> 01:08:50,940
You have to be willing to do
whatever it takes

1281
01:08:50,940 --> 01:08:54,410
- to seize your moment.
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

1282
01:08:54,410 --> 01:08:55,990
I know you understand.

1283
01:08:56,380 --> 01:08:58,930
No! No!

1284
01:08:59,250 --> 01:09:00,620
<font color="#ff00ff">(GRUNTING)</font>

1285
01:09:00,620 --> 01:09:03,550
Let go! No!

1286
01:09:03,550 --> 01:09:05,570
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCREAMING)</font>

1287
01:09:09,260 --> 01:09:11,740
<font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS AND COUGHS)</font>

1288
01:09:25,980 --> 01:09:30,310
<font color="#ff00ff">(ECHOING)</font> Help!
Can anyone hear me?

1289
01:09:30,320 --> 01:09:32,760
I want to go home.

1290
01:09:32,920 --> 01:09:35,570
<font color="#ff00ff">(PANTING)</font>

1291
01:09:47,430 --> 01:09:49,180
- <font color="#ff00ff">(RUSTLING)</font>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

1292
01:09:51,300 --> 01:09:52,970
- <font color="#ff00ff">(STAMMERS)</font> Hector?
- Kid?

1293
01:09:52,970 --> 01:09:55,840
Oh, Hector!
You were right.

1294
01:09:55,840 --> 01:09:58,440
I should have gone
back to my family.

1295
01:09:58,440 --> 01:10:01,010
They told me not
to be like de la Cruz,

1296
01:10:01,010 --> 01:10:02,850
but I didn't listen.

1297
01:10:02,850 --> 01:10:05,850
I told them I didn't care
if they remembered me.

1298
01:10:05,850 --> 01:10:09,420
I didn't care if I was
on their stupid <i>ofrenda.</i>

1299
01:10:09,420 --> 01:10:12,320
Hey, <i>chamaco.</i>
It's okay. It's okay.

1300
01:10:12,330 --> 01:10:14,940
I told them I didn't care.

1301
01:10:17,000 --> 01:10:18,630
<font color="#ff00ff">(GASPING)</font>

1302
01:10:18,630 --> 01:10:21,810
Hector! Hector?

1303
01:10:22,500 --> 01:10:25,740
She's forgetting me.

1304
01:10:25,740 --> 01:10:29,020
- Who?
- My daughter.

1305
01:10:31,440 --> 01:10:35,880
She's the reason you wanted
to cross the bridge.

1306
01:10:35,880 --> 01:10:39,380
I just wanted
to see her again.

1307
01:10:39,390 --> 01:10:42,070
I never should have
left Santa Cecilia.

1308
01:10:43,120 --> 01:10:45,120
I wish I could apologize.

1309
01:10:45,130 --> 01:10:49,130
I wish I could tell her that her
<i>papa</i> was trying to come home.

1310
01:10:49,130 --> 01:10:51,710
That he loved her so much.

1311
01:10:54,040 --> 01:10:55,950
My Coco...

1312
01:10:57,870 --> 01:10:59,690
Coco?

1313
01:11:15,560 --> 01:11:18,890
Where did you get this?

1314
01:11:18,890 --> 01:11:22,710
That's my <i>Mama</i> Coco.
That's my <i>Mama</i> Imelda.

1315
01:11:23,670 --> 01:11:26,750
Is that you?

1316
01:11:30,410 --> 01:11:33,890
- We're...
- <font color="#138ce9">BOTH:</font> Family?

1317
01:11:46,090 --> 01:11:48,790
<font color="#138ce9">HECTOR:</font> I always hoped
I'd see her again.

1318
01:11:48,790 --> 01:11:51,190
That she'd miss me.

1319
01:11:51,190 --> 01:11:55,280
Maybe put up my photo.
But it never happened.

1320
01:11:56,440 --> 01:11:58,570
You know the worst part?

1321
01:11:58,570 --> 01:12:00,840
Even if I never got to see
Coco in the living world...

1322
01:12:00,840 --> 01:12:04,440
I thought at least
one day I'd see her here.

1323
01:12:04,440 --> 01:12:06,160
Give her the biggest hug.

1324
01:12:08,110 --> 01:12:11,950
But she's the last person
who remembers me.

1325
01:12:11,950 --> 01:12:14,220
The moment she's gone
from the living world...

1326
01:12:14,220 --> 01:12:18,120
You disappear...
from this one.

1327
01:12:18,120 --> 01:12:19,990
You'll never get to see her.

1328
01:12:19,990 --> 01:12:22,010
Ever again.

1329
01:12:25,000 --> 01:12:28,130
You know,
I wrote her a song once.

1330
01:12:28,130 --> 01:12:32,140
We used to sing it every
night at the same time.

1331
01:12:32,140 --> 01:12:34,890
No matter
how far apart we were.

1332
01:12:35,840 --> 01:12:38,510
What I wouldn't give
to sing it to her

1333
01:12:38,510 --> 01:12:41,460
one... last... time.

1334
01:12:43,480 --> 01:12:47,180
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪ Remember me</i></font>

1335
01:12:47,190 --> 01:12:52,040
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪ Though I have to say
goodbye Remember me</i></font>

1336
01:12:52,990 --> 01:12:56,030
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪ Don't let it make you cry</i></font>

1337
01:12:56,030 --> 01:13:01,900
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪ For even if I'm far away
I hold you in my heart</i></font>

1338
01:13:01,900 --> 01:13:07,850
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪ I sing a secret song to
you Each night we are apart</i></font>

1339
01:13:08,780 --> 01:13:11,140
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪ Remember me</i></font>

1340
01:13:11,140 --> 01:13:12,480
<i>Papa!</i>

1341
01:13:12,480 --> 01:13:16,830
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪ Though I have to
travel far Remember me</i></font>

1342
01:13:17,680 --> 01:13:21,620
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪ Each time
you hear a sad guitar</i></font>

1343
01:13:21,620 --> 01:13:27,510
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪ Know that I'm with you
The only way that I can be</i></font>

1344
01:13:29,660 --> 01:13:34,150
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪ Until you're in
my arms again</i></font>

1345
01:13:36,070 --> 01:13:42,820
<i><font color="#ffff00">♪ Remember me </font><font color="#ffff00">♪</i></font>

1346
01:13:48,580 --> 01:13:52,690
He stole your guitar.
He stole your songs.

1347
01:13:52,690 --> 01:13:56,320
You should be the one the world
remembers, not de la Cruz!

1348
01:13:56,320 --> 01:13:59,090
I didn't write <i>Remember Me</i>
for the world.

1349
01:13:59,090 --> 01:14:01,010
I wrote it for Coco.

1350
01:14:02,700 --> 01:14:05,700
I'm a pretty sorry excuse
for a great-great-grandpa.

1351
01:14:05,700 --> 01:14:08,970
Are you kidding? A minute ago I
thought I was related to a murderer.

1352
01:14:08,970 --> 01:14:11,240
You're a total upgrade.

1353
01:14:11,240 --> 01:14:13,880
My whole life,
there's been something...

1354
01:14:13,880 --> 01:14:15,610
that made me different.

1355
01:14:15,610 --> 01:14:17,900
And I never knew
where it came from.

1356
01:14:18,720 --> 01:14:22,250
But now I know.
It comes from you.

1357
01:14:22,250 --> 01:14:27,120
I'm proud we're family!
I'm proud to be his family!

1358
01:14:27,120 --> 01:14:28,870
<font color="#ff00ff">(WHOOPING)</font>

1359
01:14:30,990 --> 01:14:33,440
<font color="#ff00ff">(WHOOPING)</font>

1360
01:14:34,130 --> 01:14:36,900
I'm proud to be
his family!

1361
01:14:36,900 --> 01:14:39,730
<font color="#ff00ff">(WHOOPING)</font>

1362
01:14:39,740 --> 01:14:41,950
<font color="#ff00ff">(ECHOING)</font>

1363
01:14:47,310 --> 01:14:50,030
<font color="#ff00ff">(DANTE HOWLING)</font>

1364
01:14:51,850 --> 01:14:53,750
Dante?

1365
01:14:53,750 --> 01:14:56,190
- <font color="#ff00ff">(BARKS)</font>
- Dante!

1366
01:14:56,190 --> 01:14:58,200
<font color="#ff00ff">(BARKING)</font>

1367
01:14:58,760 --> 01:15:00,340
It's Dante!

1368
01:15:02,190 --> 01:15:03,580
<font color="#ff00ff">(ROARS)</font>

1369
01:15:05,060 --> 01:15:06,380
<font color="#ff00ff">(LAUGHS)</font>

1370
01:15:06,630 --> 01:15:09,080
<font color="#ff00ff">(LAUGHING)</font>

1371
01:15:11,940 --> 01:15:15,220
- Imelda!
- Hector.

1372
01:15:15,640 --> 01:15:17,220
You look good.

1373
01:15:22,820 --> 01:15:25,060
<font color="#ff00ff">(WHIMPERS)</font>

1374
01:15:27,050 --> 01:15:28,390
<font color="#ff00ff">(ROARS)</font>

1375
01:15:28,390 --> 01:15:31,660
Dante! You knew he was my
<i>Papa</i> Hector the whole time!

1376
01:15:31,660 --> 01:15:33,660
You are a real spirit guide.

1377
01:15:33,660 --> 01:15:36,190
Who's the good spirit guide?
You are!

1378
01:15:36,200 --> 01:15:37,430
<font color="#ff00ff">(LAUGHS)</font>

1379
01:15:37,430 --> 01:15:40,150
<font color="#ff00ff">(WHINING)</font>

1380
01:15:43,200 --> 01:15:44,520
<font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

1381
01:15:47,110 --> 01:15:48,420
Whoa!

1382
01:15:50,910 --> 01:15:52,530
- <font color="#ff00ff">(LAUGHS)</font>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(BARKS)</font>

1383
01:15:55,820 --> 01:15:57,360
Dante!

1384
01:15:57,820 --> 01:15:59,370
<font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

1385
01:16:00,220 --> 01:16:02,140
<font color="#ff00ff">(BARKING)</font>

1386
01:16:09,800 --> 01:16:12,250
<font color="#ff00ff">(ROARS)</font>

1387
01:16:21,010 --> 01:16:22,310
There they are!

1388
01:16:22,310 --> 01:16:26,660
<font color="#138ce9">ALL:</font> Miguel! Miguelito! Look, it's Miguel!
He's all right.

1389
01:16:28,120 --> 01:16:31,170
<i>Gracias, Dios mio.
Que bueno.</i>

1390
01:16:31,390 --> 01:16:32,700
<font color="#ff00ff">(GROANS)</font>

1391
01:16:34,420 --> 01:16:36,170
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCOFFS)</font>

1392
01:16:37,960 --> 01:16:39,440
<font color="#ff00ff">(BARKS)</font>

1393
01:16:42,770 --> 01:16:44,000
<font color="#ff00ff">(YELPS)</font>

1394
01:16:44,000 --> 01:16:45,270
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLES)</font>

1395
01:16:45,270 --> 01:16:47,300
<i>Mijo,</i> I was so worried!

1396
01:16:47,300 --> 01:16:49,550
Thank goodness
we found you in time.

1397
01:16:50,510 --> 01:16:54,040
And you... How many times
must I turn you away?

1398
01:16:54,040 --> 01:16:55,310
Imelda.

1399
01:16:55,310 --> 01:16:58,510
I want nothing to do with you!
Not in life, not in death!

1400
01:16:58,520 --> 01:17:02,150
I spent decades protecting
my family from your mistakes.

1401
01:17:02,150 --> 01:17:04,150
He spends
five minutes with you

1402
01:17:04,150 --> 01:17:05,890
and I have to fish him
out of a sinkhole!

1403
01:17:05,890 --> 01:17:07,420
I wasn't in there
because of Hector.

1404
01:17:07,430 --> 01:17:10,060
He was in there
because of me.

1405
01:17:10,060 --> 01:17:12,330
He was just
trying to get me home!

1406
01:17:12,330 --> 01:17:16,800
I didn't want to listen,
but he was right.

1407
01:17:16,800 --> 01:17:19,080
Nothing's more
important than family.

1408
01:17:20,040 --> 01:17:22,720
I'm ready
to accept your blessing.

1409
01:17:23,140 --> 01:17:25,170
And your conditions.

1410
01:17:25,180 --> 01:17:27,480
But first,
I need to find de la Cruz.

1411
01:17:27,480 --> 01:17:29,340
To get Hector's photo.

1412
01:17:29,350 --> 01:17:31,050
- What?
- So he can see Coco again.

1413
01:17:31,050 --> 01:17:32,950
Hector should be
on our <i>ofrenda.</i>

1414
01:17:32,950 --> 01:17:34,420
He's part of our family.

1415
01:17:34,420 --> 01:17:35,890
He left this family!

1416
01:17:35,890 --> 01:17:37,550
He tried to go home
to you and Coco.

1417
01:17:37,560 --> 01:17:39,540
But de la Cruz
murdered him!

1418
01:17:40,490 --> 01:17:42,340
It's true, Imelda.

1419
01:17:43,100 --> 01:17:44,560
And so what if it's true?

1420
01:17:44,560 --> 01:17:47,060
You leave me alone
with a child to raise...

1421
01:17:47,070 --> 01:17:49,170
and I'm just
supposed to forgive you?

1422
01:17:49,170 --> 01:17:51,100
Imelda, I... <font color="#ff00ff">(GROANS)</font>

1423
01:17:51,100 --> 01:17:53,340
- Hector!
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

1424
01:17:53,340 --> 01:17:54,940
<font color="#ff00ff">(BREATHES SHAKILY)</font>

1425
01:17:54,940 --> 01:17:58,690
I'm running out of time.
It's Coco.

1426
01:17:59,850 --> 01:18:01,530
She's forgetting you.

1427
01:18:02,480 --> 01:18:05,320
You don't have
to forgive him.

1428
01:18:05,320 --> 01:18:07,630
But we shouldn't
forget him.

1429
01:18:10,060 --> 01:18:13,460
I wanted to forget you.

1430
01:18:13,460 --> 01:18:16,360
I wanted Coco
to forget you too, but...

1431
01:18:16,360 --> 01:18:19,410
This is my fault.
Not yours.

1432
01:18:21,470 --> 01:18:23,620
I'm sorry, Imelda.

1433
01:18:27,510 --> 01:18:31,240
Miguel, if we help you
get his photo,

1434
01:18:31,250 --> 01:18:32,980
you will return home?

1435
01:18:32,980 --> 01:18:34,560
No more music?

1436
01:18:35,520 --> 01:18:38,170
Family comes first.

1437
01:18:39,850 --> 01:18:43,300
I can't forgive you.

1438
01:18:45,530 --> 01:18:47,480
But I will help you.

1439
01:18:48,430 --> 01:18:51,410
So, how do we get
to de la Cruz?

1440
01:18:52,370 --> 01:18:55,180
I might know a way.

1441
01:18:57,010 --> 01:18:59,450
<font color="#ff00ff">(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

1442
01:19:05,280 --> 01:19:08,430
<font color="#ff00ff">(AUDIENCE CHEERING)</font>

1443
01:19:10,550 --> 01:19:12,370
<font color="#ffff00">♪ </font><font color="#ffff00">♪</font>

1444
01:19:19,900 --> 01:19:21,310
<font color="#ff00ff">(MUSIC STOPS)</font>

1445
01:19:23,400 --> 01:19:25,450
<font color="#ff00ff">(SPOOKY MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

1446
01:19:45,590 --> 01:19:48,210
- Good luck, <i>muchacho.</i>
- <i>Gracias,</i> Frida.

1447
01:19:49,290 --> 01:19:51,640
<font color="#ff00ff">(ALL GRUNTING)</font>

1448
01:19:53,060 --> 01:19:54,930
- <font color="#ff00ff">(SCREAMS IN PAIN)</font>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(YELPS)</font>

1449
01:19:54,930 --> 01:19:56,700
<font color="#ff00ff">(PANTING)</font>

1450
01:19:56,700 --> 01:19:59,970
- Here, let me help you with...
- Don't touch me!

1451
01:19:59,970 --> 01:20:02,240
- Everyone clear on the plan?
- Find Hector's photo.

1452
01:20:02,240 --> 01:20:04,070
- Give it to Miguel.
- Send Miguel home.

1453
01:20:04,080 --> 01:20:05,930
- Got your petals?
- <font color="#ff00ff">(BARKS)</font>

1454
01:20:06,950 --> 01:20:08,580
Now, we just
have to find de la Cruz.

1455
01:20:08,580 --> 01:20:09,890
- Yes?
- <font color="#ff00ff">(SCREAMS)</font>

1456
01:20:10,720 --> 01:20:12,670
Don't I know you?

1457
01:20:13,520 --> 01:20:16,250
That's for murdering
the love of my life!

1458
01:20:16,260 --> 01:20:18,320
- Who... Who the...
- She's talking about me!

1459
01:20:18,320 --> 01:20:19,620
I'm the love of your life?

1460
01:20:19,630 --> 01:20:21,390
I don't know.
I'm still angry at you.

1461
01:20:21,390 --> 01:20:22,730
Hector!
How did you... <font color="#ff00ff">(GROANS)</font>

1462
01:20:22,730 --> 01:20:25,660
And that's for trying
to murder my grandson.

1463
01:20:25,670 --> 01:20:28,070
- Grandson?
- She's talking about me!

1464
01:20:28,070 --> 01:20:32,240
You! Wait.
You're related to Hector?

1465
01:20:32,240 --> 01:20:33,790
The photo!

1466
01:20:35,510 --> 01:20:37,140
Uh...

1467
01:20:37,140 --> 01:20:38,860
After him!

1468
01:20:39,610 --> 01:20:41,010
<font color="#ff00ff">(GROANS)</font>

1469
01:20:41,020 --> 01:20:43,220
Security! <i>Ayudenme!</i>

1470
01:20:43,220 --> 01:20:46,280
- You said love of your life.
- I don't know what I said.

1471
01:20:46,290 --> 01:20:47,700
That's what I heard.

1472
01:20:49,990 --> 01:20:52,270
<font color="#ff00ff">(GRUNTING)</font>

1473
01:21:01,000 --> 01:21:02,980
Places, <i>Senor.</i>
You're on in thirty seconds.

1474
01:21:04,240 --> 01:21:06,350
<font color="#ff00ff">(BOTH GRUNTING)</font>

1475
01:21:07,270 --> 01:21:08,760
- <font color="#ff00ff">(MAMA IMELDA YELPS)</font>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GASPS)</font>

1476
01:21:09,540 --> 01:21:12,460
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GRUNTS)</font>
- <i>Ay!</i> Miguel! I have it!

1477
01:21:12,680 --> 01:21:14,000
<font color="#ff00ff">(YELPS)</font>

1478
01:21:15,550 --> 01:21:17,600
- <font color="#ff00ff">(RUMBLING)</font>
- <font color="#ff00ff">(YELPS)</font>

1479
01:21:21,160 --> 01:21:22,470
Oh!

1480
01:21:25,560 --> 01:21:26,970
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCREAMS)</font>

1481
01:21:28,400 --> 01:21:30,010
<font color="#138ce9">MIGUEL:</font> Hurry! Come on!

1482
01:21:31,400 --> 01:21:33,700
<font color="#138ce9">EMCEE:</font> <i>Ladies and gentlemen...</i>

1483
01:21:33,700 --> 01:21:39,570
<i>the one... the only...
Ernesto de la Cruz!</i>

1484
01:21:39,570 --> 01:21:42,920
<font color="#ff00ff">(AUDIENCE CHEERING)</font>

1485
01:21:48,480 --> 01:21:49,720
Get her off the stage.

1486
01:21:49,720 --> 01:21:52,470
<font color="#ff00ff">(PANTING)</font>

1487
01:21:56,330 --> 01:21:58,430
<font color="#ff00ff">(BREATHING HEAVILY)</font>

1488
